                        General Henry A. Byroade, at Peiping</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d315</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">315</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="315" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Brigadier
                        General <persName type="to">Henry A. Byroade</persName>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-04">4 May
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>638. Want you to proceed urgently to Hankow on 5 May (tomorrow) to reach there by
                    about noon. Bring an extra field team. More follows in code.<note n="14" xml:id="d315fn14">See telegram No. 636, May 4, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
